article.headline: Pennsylvania 74, Brown 68 (OT)
article.story: PROVIDENCE, R.I. (AP) -- Ibrahim Jaaber converted 5-of-6 free throws in the last 18.1 seconds of overtime as Pennsylvania rallied for a 74-68 victory over Brown on Saturday night. Brown (10-17, 6-8 Ivy League) led 66-65 on a free throw by Mark MacDonald, but Steve Danley put Penn ahead for good by sinking back-to-back jump shots. Mark Zoller led the Quakers (20-7, 12-1) with 17 points and 10 rebounds, Eric Osmundson contributed 15 points, all on 3-point shots, while Jaabar and Steve Grandieri each finished with 13. Keenan Jeppesen led the Bears with a game-high 21 points and freshman Scott Friske scored 13. Penn led 60-57 when Brown's Marcus Becker blocked a shot by Grandieri, then buried a 3-point shot at the buzzer to force overtime. Brown led by as many as 12 points in the first half, the last time at 30-18. Penn pulled within 32-24 at halftime and took its first lead of the game, 39-38, on a 3-point shot by Osmundson early in the second half. The Quakers, who have already clinched the league title, have won five in a row and 10 of their last 11 games.
